This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with automated architecture search for neural networks. Additionally, the paper focuses on language modeling and machine translation, which are sub-fields of natural language processing (NLP) falling under the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also introduces non-standard RNN components, which could fall under the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper could also be relevant to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) as RNNs are commonly used in image and video processing tasks.
